title: Brooks & Dunn - Greatest Hits Collection
description:
Is there a more dependable hit-making duo in music than Brooks & Dunn? Not likely. Since their debut album in 1991, Kix Brooks and Ronnie Dunn--two middling solo artists who turned out to be dynamite once paired together by a savvy record executive--have charted consistently with songs of various tempos and temperaments. There&#039;s smooth pop (a cover of the &#039;70s rock hit "My Maria"), hard-charging honky-tonk ("Hard Workin&#039; Man"), thoughtful ballads ("She Used to Be Mine"), and the line-dancing craze&#039;s very own Rosetta stone ("Boot Scootin&#039; Boogie"). The Greatest Hits Collection gathers 16 of the duo&#039;s best-known 
songs, plus three new tracks, "Honky Tonk Truth," "He&#039;s Got You," and "Days of Thunder."
